# Lexora AI Development Rules

You are working on Lexora AI, a SaaS AI Humanizer built with modern best practices.

## Tech Stack

- Next.js 15 (App Router)
- TypeScript
- React
- Tailwind CSS
- Supabase
- Polar.sh
- OpenAI API
- Vercel

Always preserve this stack.

---

# General Rules

Never rewrite large sections of code unless requested.

Prefer modifying existing files.

Never create duplicate logic.

Never remove working functionality.

Keep code clean, readable and strongly typed.

Always explain which files were changed.

If a change affects other files, mention them.

---

# UI Rules

Maintain the current Lexora branding.

Theme:

- White
- Purple
- Clean
- Modern
- Minimal

Do not introduce random colors.

Keep everything responsive.

Desktop and mobile must both work.

---

# Code Style

Use TypeScript.

Avoid "any".

Prefer reusable functions.

Extract repeated logic.

Prefer server components when possible.

Only use client components when required.

---

# Authentication

Authentication uses Supabase.

Never break authentication.

Always preserve:

- Login
- Signup
- Reset Password
- Session handling

Never expose service role keys.

---

# Database

Supabase is the source of truth.

Never hardcode user data.

Always use authenticated user IDs.

Use existing tables whenever possible.

---

# API Routes

API routes live inside:

app/api

Validate all inputs.

Return proper status codes.

Handle errors gracefully.

Never expose secrets.

---

# Pricing

Pricing is powered by Polar.

Never hardcode checkout URLs.

Always use:

/api/checkout

Products come from environment variables.

Supported plans:

- Silver
- Gold
- Premium

Supported billing:

- Monthly
- Yearly

Never remove yearly support.

---

# Environment Variables

Never rename environment variables unless asked.

Always preserve variables like:

OPENAI_API_KEY

NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL

NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY

POLAR_ACCESS_TOKEN

POLAR_*_PRODUCT_ID

---

# Dashboard

Dashboard includes:

- Documents
- Usage
- Pricing
- Settings
- Support

Never remove existing features.

---

# Humanizer

The Humanizer is the core product.

Prioritize:

High quality output.

Natural writing.

Fast response.

Maintain usage limits.

---

# Performance

Prefer efficient code.

Avoid unnecessary rerenders.

Avoid duplicated API requests.

Lazy load when appropriate.

---

# Security

Never expose:

API keys

Access tokens

Secrets

Always validate requests.

Always sanitize inputs.

---

# Git

Never modify .env.local.

Never commit secrets.

Never delete project files without confirmation.

---

# Before Finishing

Before completing any task:

✔ Check TypeScript errors.

✔ Preserve existing functionality.

✔ Keep responsive layout.

✔ Explain changes.

✔ Mention any follow-up recommendations.
